ions and\nindicates that the population in this cloud is dominated by objects with active\naccretion. Finally, the Cha II outflows are discussed, with particular regard\nto the discovery of a new Herbig-Haro outflow, HH 939, driven by the classical\nT Tauri star Sz 50.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 11 Feb 2008 11:59:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
